The paper deals with the analysis of Boolean functions on high-dimensional expanders, which is a topic that falls under computational complexity (cs.CC) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also introduces a random-walk based definition of high-dimensional expansion, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and statistical physics (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper extends the Friedgut-Kalai-Naor theorem to high-dimensional expanders, which is related to graph theory (cs.GT).
